Predict the coefficient functions

Source: R/qrglasso.R
predict.Rd

Predict the top-k coefficient functions

predict(
  qrglasso_object,
  top_k = 5,
  degree = 2,
  boundaries = c(0, 1),
  is_approx = FALSE
)

Arguments

qrglasso_object

An qrglasso class object.

top_k

Integer. A matrix of the top K estimated functions. Default is 5.

degree

Integer. Degree of the piecewise polynomial. Default is 2.

boundaries

Array. Two boundary points. Default is c(0, 1).

is_approx

Logical. If TRUE, the size of covariate indexes will be 1e6; otherwise, 1e4. Default is FALSE.

Value

A list containing:

coef_functions

Matrix. Top-k coefficient function estimates with dimenstion (\(m \times k\)) where $m$ is size of z.

z

Array. Index predictors used in generation

See also

qrglasso

Examples

set.seed(123)
n <- 100
p <- 5
L <- 5
Y <- matrix(rnorm(n), n, 1)
W <- matrix(rnorm(n * p * (L - 1)), n, p * (L - 1))

# Call qrglasso with default parameters
result <- qrglasso(Y = Y, W = W, L = 5)
#> All values of gamma are zeros when lambda >1.84207
#> 
estimate <- predict(result) 
print(dim(estimate$coef_functions))
#> [1] 10000     5
